{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"Let's talk about trust."},{"time":4240,"text":"We all know trust is fundamental,"},{"time":7760,"text":"but when it comes to trusting people,"},{"time":10400,"text":"something profound is happening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":13800,"text":"Please raise your hand"},{"time":15080,"text":"if you have ever been\na host or a guest on Airbnb."},{"time":20400,"text":"Wow. That's a lot of you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23640,"text":"Who owns Bitcoin?"},{"time":26640,"text":"Still a lot of you. OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27920,"text":"And please raise your hand\nif you've ever used Tinder"},{"time":30640,"text":"to help you find a mate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32280,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":34120,"text":"This one's really hard to count\nbecause you're kind of going like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":39360,"text":"These are all examples of how technology"},{"time":42160,"text":"is creating new mechanisms"},{"time":44280,"text":"that are enabling us to trust\nunknown people, companies and ideas."},{"time":50320,"text":"And yet at the same time,"},{"time":52360,"text":"trust in institutions --"},{"time":53920,"text":"banks, governments and even churches --"},{"time":56880,"text":"is collapsing."},{"time":58280,"text":"So what's happening here,"},{"time":60520,"text":"and who do you trust?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":62800,"text":"Let's start in France with a platform --\nwith a company, I should say --"},{"time":66720,"text":"with a rather funny-sounding name,"},{"time":68880,"text":"BlaBlaCar."},{"time":70160,"text":"It's a platform that matches\ndrivers and passengers"},{"time":73800,"text":"who want to share\nlong-distance journeys together."},{"time":77840,"text":"The average ride taken is 320 kilometers."},{"time":82080,"text":"So it's a good idea\nto choose your fellow travelers wisely."},{"time":87320,"text":"Social profiles and reviews\nhelp people make a choice."},{"time":91320,"text":"You can see if someone's a smoker,\nyou can see what kind of music they like,"},{"time":96360,"text":"you can see if they're going to bring\ntheir dog along for the ride."},{"time":100440,"text":"But it turns out\nthat the key social identifier"},{"time":104040,"text":"is how much you're going\nto talk in the car."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":108520,"text":"Bla, not a lot,"},{"time":110160,"text":"bla bla, you want a nice bit of chitchat,"},{"time":112480,"text":"and bla bla bla, you're not going\nto stop talking the entire way"},{"time":116240,"text":"from London to Paris."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117720,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":120040,"text":"It's remarkable, right,\nthat this idea works at all,"},{"time":123080,"text":"because it's counter to the lesson\nmost of us were taught as a child:"},{"time":126960,"text":"never get in a car with a stranger."},{"time":129680,"text":"And yet, BlaBlaCar transports\nmore than four million people"},{"time":134840,"text":"every single month."},{"time":136880,"text":"To put that in context,\nthat's more passengers"},{"time":139240,"text":"than the Eurostar\nor JetBlue airlines carry."},{"time":143360,"text":"BlaBlaCar is a beautiful illustration\nof how technology is enabling"},{"time":147520,"text":"millions of people across the world\nto take a trust leap."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151560,"text":"A trust leap happens when we take the risk\nto do something new or different"},{"time":157840,"text":"to the way that we've always done it."},{"time":160440,"text":"Let's try to visualize this together."},{"time":163360,"text":"OK. I want you to close your eyes."},{"time":167320,"text":"There is a man staring at me\nwith his eyes wide open."},{"time":170400,"text":"I'm on this big red circle. I can see."},{"time":172880,"text":"So close your eyes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174320,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":177200,"text":"I'll do it with you."},{"time":178480,"text":"And I want you to imagine\nthere exists a gap"},{"time":181520,"text":"between you and something unknown."},{"time":184760,"text":"That unknown can be\nsomeone you've just met."},{"time":187640,"text":"It can be a place you've never been to."},{"time":189760,"text":"It can be something\nyou've never tried before."},{"time":193160,"text":"You got it?"},{"time":194400,"text":"OK. You can open your eyes now."},{"time":196520,"text":"For you to leap from a place of certainty,"},{"time":199880,"text":"to take a chance on that someone\nor something unknown,"},{"time":203480,"text":"you need a force to pull you over the gap,"},{"time":206840,"text":"and that remarkable force is trust."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210560,"text":"Trust is an elusive concept,"},{"time":214200,"text":"and yet we depend on it\nfor our lives to function."},{"time":217600,"text":"I trust my children"},{"time":219880,"text":"when they say they're going\nto turn the lights out at night."},{"time":222760,"text":"I trusted the pilot\nwho flew me here to keep me safe."},{"time":226000,"text":"It's a word we use a lot,"},{"time":228840,"text":"without always thinking\nabout what it really means"},{"time":231280,"text":"and how it works in different\ncontexts of our lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234680,"text":"There are, in fact,\nhundreds of definitions of trust,"},{"time":238320,"text":"and most can be reduced\nto some kind of risk assessment"},{"time":242920,"text":"of how likely it is\nthat things will go right."},{"time":246120,"text":"But I don't like this definition of trust,"},{"time":248720,"text":"because it makes trust\nsound rational and predictable,"},{"time":253040,"text":"and it doesn't really get\nto the human essence"},{"time":255640,"text":"of what it enables us to do"},{"time":257600,"text":"and how it empowers us"},{"time":259600,"text":"to connect with other people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261720,"text":"So I define trust a little differently."},{"time":263800,"text":"I define trust as a confident\nrelationship to the unknown."},{"time":269920,"text":"Now, when you view trust\nthrough this lens,"},{"time":272040,"text":"it starts to explain\nwhy it has the unique capacity"},{"time":275720,"text":"to enable us to cope with uncertainty,"},{"time":278840,"text":"to place our faith in strangers,"},{"time":281880,"text":"to keep moving forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284400,"text":"Human beings are remarkable"},{"time":287200,"text":"at taking trust leaps."},{"time":289400,"text":"Do you remember the first time\nyou put your credit card details"},{"time":292400,"text":"into a website?"},{"time":293640,"text":"That's a trust leap."},{"time":295000,"text":"I distinctly remember telling my dad"},{"time":297960,"text":"that I wanted to buy a navy blue\nsecondhand Peugeot on eBay,"},{"time":303240,"text":"and he rightfully pointed out"},{"time":304920,"text":"that the seller's name\nwas \"Invisible Wizard\""},{"time":307320,"text":"and that this probably\nwas not such a good idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310440,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":312160,"text":"So my work, my research\nfocuses on how technology"},{"time":315600,"text":"is transforming\nthe social glue of society,"},{"time":318280,"text":"trust between people,"},{"time":319960,"text":"and it's a fascinating area to study,"},{"time":322240,"text":"because there's still\nso much we do not know."},{"time":325640,"text":"For instance, do men and women\ntrust differently in digital environments?"},{"time":330760,"text":"Does the way we build trust\nface-to-face translate online?"},{"time":335680,"text":"Does trust transfer?"},{"time":337640,"text":"So if you trust finding a mate on Tinder,"},{"time":340360,"text":"are you more likely\nto trust finding a ride on BlaBlaCar?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":344440,"text":"But from studying hundreds\nof networks and marketplaces,"},{"time":347720,"text":"there is a common pattern\nthat people follow,"},{"time":350560,"text":"and I call it \"climbing the trust stack.\""},{"time":353240,"text":"Let me use BlaBlaCar\nas an example to bring it to life."},{"time":357080,"text":"On the first level,"},{"time":358400,"text":"you have to trust the idea."},{"time":360600,"text":"So you have to trust"},{"time":361840,"text":"the idea of ride-sharing\nis safe and worth trying."},{"time":365640,"text":"The second level is about having\nconfidence in the platform,"},{"time":370360,"text":"that BlaBlaCar will help you\nif something goes wrong."},{"time":374520,"text":"And the third level is about\nusing little bits of information"},{"time":378200,"text":"to decide whether\nthe other person is trustworthy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382200,"text":"Now, the first time\nwe climb the trust stack,"},{"time":384840,"text":"it feels weird, even risky,"},{"time":388120,"text":"but we get to a point\nwhere these ideas seem totally normal."},{"time":393120,"text":"Our behaviors transform,"},{"time":395440,"text":"often relatively quickly."},{"time":397440,"text":"In other words, trust enables\nchange and innovation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403280,"text":"So an idea that intrigued me,\nand I'd like you to consider,"},{"time":406720,"text":"is whether we can better understand"},{"time":409280,"text":"major waves of disruption and change\nin individuals in society"},{"time":413480,"text":"through the lens of trust."},{"time":415560,"text":"Well, it turns out\nthat trust has only evolved"},{"time":418880,"text":"in three significant chapters\nthroughout the course of human history:"},{"time":423560,"text":"local, institutional"},{"time":425800,"text":"and what we're now entering, distributed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428680,"text":"So for a long time,"},{"time":431040,"text":"until the mid-1800s,"},{"time":432320,"text":"trust was built\naround tight-knit relationships."},{"time":436280,"text":"So say I lived in a village"},{"time":438320,"text":"with the first five rows of this audience,"},{"time":440920,"text":"and we all knew one another,"},{"time":442880,"text":"and say I wanted to borrow money."},{"time":445800,"text":"The man who had his eyes wide open,\nhe might lend it to me,"},{"time":448800,"text":"and if I didn't pay him back,"},{"time":450920,"text":"you'd all know I was dodgy."},{"time":452600,"text":"I would get a bad reputation,"},{"time":454280,"text":"and you would refuse\nto do business with me in the future."},{"time":457360,"text":"Trust was mostly local\nand accountability-based."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461600,"text":"In the mid-19th century,"},{"time":462960,"text":"society went through\na tremendous amount of change."},{"time":466400,"text":"People moved to fast-growing cities\nsuch as London and San Francisco,"},{"time":470200,"text":"and a local banker here\nwas replaced by large corporations"},{"time":475080,"text":"that didn't know us as individuals."},{"time":478000,"text":"We started to place our trust"},{"time":480000,"text":"into black box systems of authority,"},{"time":483600,"text":"things like legal contracts\nand regulation and insurance,"},{"time":487920,"text":"and less trust directly in other people."},{"time":491960,"text":"Trust became institutional\nand commission-based."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495840,"text":"It's widely talked about how trust\nin institutions and many corporate brands"},{"time":500680,"text":"has been steadily declining\nand continues to do so."},{"time":504440,"text":"I am constantly stunned\nby major breaches of trust:"},{"time":510080,"text":"the News Corp phone hacking,"},{"time":512600,"text":"the Volkswagen emissions scandal,"},{"time":515440,"text":"the widespread abuse\nin the Catholic Church,"},{"time":518799,"text":"the fact that only one measly banker"},{"time":522039,"text":"went to jail after the great\nfinancial crisis,"},{"time":525360,"text":"or more recently the Panama Papers"},{"time":527440,"text":"that revealed how the rich\ncan exploit offshore tax regimes."},{"time":532600,"text":"And the thing that really surprises me"},{"time":535080,"text":"is why do leaders find it so hard"},{"time":539120,"text":"to apologize, I mean sincerely apologize,"},{"time":542320,"text":"when our trust is broken?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":545360,"text":"It would be easy to conclude\nthat institutional trust isn't working"},{"time":549520,"text":"because we are fed up"},{"time":551040,"text":"with the sheer audacity\nof dishonest elites,"},{"time":553960,"text":"but what's happening now"},{"time":555960,"text":"runs deeper than the rampant questioning\nof the size and structure of institutions."},{"time":561600,"text":"We're starting to realize"},{"time":563640,"text":"that institutional trust"},{"time":565440,"text":"wasn't designed for the digital age."},{"time":568440,"text":"Conventions of how trust is built,"},{"time":572120,"text":"managed, lost and repaired --"},{"time":574480,"text":"in brands, leaders and entire systems --"},{"time":577000,"text":"is being turned upside down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579760,"text":"Now, this is exciting,"},{"time":581880,"text":"but it's frightening,"},{"time":583440,"text":"because it forces many of us\nto have to rethink"},{"time":586160,"text":"how trust is built and destroyed\nwith our customers, with our employees,"},{"time":590880,"text":"even our loved ones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593800,"text":"The other day, I was talking to the CEO\nof a leading international hotel brand,"},{"time":600000,"text":"and as is often the case,\nwe got onto the topic of Airbnb."},{"time":603840,"text":"And he admitted to me\nthat he was perplexed by their success."},{"time":608960,"text":"He was perplexed at how a company"},{"time":611120,"text":"that depends on the willingness\nof strangers to trust one another"},{"time":615320,"text":"could work so well across 191 countries."},{"time":619920,"text":"So I said to him\nthat I had a confession to make,"},{"time":623080,"text":"and he looked at me a bit strangely,"},{"time":625080,"text":"and I said --"},{"time":626480,"text":"and I'm sure many of you\ndo this as well --"},{"time":628520,"text":"I don't always bother to hang my towels up"},{"time":631040,"text":"when I'm finished in the hotel,"},{"time":634000,"text":"but I would never do this\nas a guest on Airbnb."},{"time":637560,"text":"And the reason why I would never do this\nas a guest on Airbnb"},{"time":640920,"text":"is because guests know\nthat they'll be rated by hosts,"},{"time":644600,"text":"and that those ratings\nare likely to impact their ability"},{"time":648360,"text":"to transact in the future."},{"time":650680,"text":"It's a simple illustration of how\nonline trust will change our behaviors"},{"time":654920,"text":"in the real world,"},{"time":656240,"text":"make us more accountable"},{"time":658760,"text":"in ways we cannot yet even imagine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662880,"text":"I am not saying we do not need hotels"},{"time":665960,"text":"or traditional forms of authority."},{"time":668320,"text":"But what we cannot deny"},{"time":670440,"text":"is that the way trust\nflows through society is changing,"},{"time":674720,"text":"and it's creating this big shift"},{"time":677040,"text":"away from the 20th century"},{"time":678920,"text":"that was defined by institutional trust"},{"time":681760,"text":"towards the 21st century"},{"time":684280,"text":"that will be fueled by distributed trust."},{"time":687480,"text":"Trust is no longer top-down."},{"time":691680,"text":"It's being unbundled and inverted."},{"time":693800,"text":"It's no longer opaque and linear."},{"time":697160,"text":"A new recipe for trust is emerging"},{"time":700160,"text":"that once again\nis distributed amongst people"},{"time":704080,"text":"and is accountability-based."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706240,"text":"And this shift is only going to accelerate"},{"time":709680,"text":"with the emergence of the blockchain,"},{"time":712440,"text":"the innovative ledger technology\nunderpinning Bitcoin."},{"time":716800,"text":"Now let's be honest,"},{"time":719760,"text":"getting our heads around\nthe way blockchain works"},{"time":723240,"text":"is mind-blowing."},{"time":725720,"text":"And one of the reasons why\nis it involves processing"},{"time":729000,"text":"some pretty complicated concepts"},{"time":731680,"text":"with terrible names."},{"time":733200,"text":"I mean, cryptographic algorithms\nand hash functions,"},{"time":737720,"text":"and people called miners,\nwho verify transactions --"},{"time":740800,"text":"all that was created\nby this mysterious person"},{"time":744400,"text":"or persons called Satoshi Nakamoto."},{"time":747160,"text":"Now, that is a massive trust leap\nthat hasn't happened yet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752840,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":755920,"text":"But let's try to imagine this."},{"time":757400,"text":"So \"The Economist\"\neloquently described the blockchain"},{"time":761120,"text":"as the great chain\nof being sure about things."},{"time":764800,"text":"The easiest way I can describe it\nis imagine the blocks as spreadsheets,"},{"time":769880,"text":"and they are filled with assets."},{"time":772880,"text":"So that could be a property title."},{"time":775320,"text":"It could be a stock trade."},{"time":777360,"text":"It could be a creative asset,\nsuch as the rights to a song."},{"time":780960,"text":"Every time something moves"},{"time":784000,"text":"from one place on the register\nto somewhere else,"},{"time":787840,"text":"that asset transfer is time-stamped"},{"time":790960,"text":"and publicly recorded on the blockchain."},{"time":794400,"text":"It's that simple. Right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796720,"text":"So the real implication of the blockchain"},{"time":799840,"text":"is that it removes the need\nfor any kind of third party,"},{"time":804000,"text":"such as a lawyer,"},{"time":805360,"text":"or a trusted intermediary,\nor maybe not a government intermediary"},{"time":808840,"text":"to facilitate the exchange."},{"time":810680,"text":"So if we go back to the trust stack,"},{"time":812960,"text":"you still have to trust the idea,"},{"time":815720,"text":"you have to trust the platform,"},{"time":818040,"text":"but you don't have to trust\nthe other person"},{"time":821000,"text":"in the traditional sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822960,"text":"The implications are huge."},{"time":825480,"text":"In the same way the internet blew open\nthe doors to an age of information"},{"time":829200,"text":"available to everyone,"},{"time":830640,"text":"the blockchain will revolutionize\ntrust on a global scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":836240,"text":"Now, I've waited to the end\nintentionally to mention Uber,"},{"time":840200,"text":"because I recognize\nthat it is a contentious"},{"time":843680,"text":"and widely overused example,"},{"time":846320,"text":"but in the context of a new era of trust,\nit's a great case study."},{"time":849920,"text":"Now, we will see cases of abuse\nof distributed trust."},{"time":854680,"text":"We've already seen this,\nand it can go horribly wrong."},{"time":858360,"text":"I am not surprised that we are seeing\nprotests from taxi associations"},{"time":863560,"text":"all around the world"},{"time":864920,"text":"trying to get governments to ban Uber\nbased on claims that it is unsafe."},{"time":870320,"text":"I happened to be in London\nthe day that these protests took place,"},{"time":874720,"text":"and I happened to notice a tweet"},{"time":876720,"text":"from Matt Hancock, who is\na British minister for business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":880360,"text":"And he wrote,"},{"time":881600,"text":"\"Does anyone have details of this\n#Uber app everyone's talking about?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":885600,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":887880,"text":"I'd never heard of it until today.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":891560,"text":"Now, the taxi associations,"},{"time":895800,"text":"they legitimized the first layer\nof the trust stack."},{"time":898560,"text":"They legitimized the idea\nthat they were trying to eliminate,"},{"time":901920,"text":"and sign-ups increased\nby 850 percent in 24 hours."},{"time":907080,"text":"Now, this is a really strong illustration"},{"time":910360,"text":"of how once a trust shift has happened\naround a behavior or an entire sector,"},{"time":916200,"text":"you cannot reverse the story."},{"time":919120,"text":"Every day, five million people\nwill take a trust leap"},{"time":923000,"text":"and ride with Uber."},{"time":924560,"text":"In China, on Didi,\nthe ride-sharing platform,"},{"time":927800,"text":"11 million rides taken every day."},{"time":930720,"text":"That's 127 rides per second,"},{"time":934360,"text":"showing that this is\na cross-cultural phenomenon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":937200,"text":"And the fascinating thing is\nthat both drivers and passengers report"},{"time":941400,"text":"that seeing a name"},{"time":943920,"text":"and seeing someone's photo\nand their rating"},{"time":946920,"text":"makes them feel safer,"},{"time":949200,"text":"and as you may have experienced,"},{"time":950800,"text":"even behave a little more nicely\nin the taxi cab."},{"time":955360,"text":"Uber and Didi are early\nbut powerful examples"},{"time":959080,"text":"of how technology\nis creating trust between people"},{"time":963080,"text":"in ways and on a scale\nnever possible before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":967120,"text":"Today, many of us are comfortable\ngetting into cars driven by strangers."},{"time":973200,"text":"We meet up with someone\nwe swiped right to be matched with."},{"time":977520,"text":"We share our homes\nwith people we do not know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":981480,"text":"This is just the beginning,"},{"time":984440,"text":"because the real disruption happening"},{"time":987040,"text":"isn't technological."},{"time":989000,"text":"It's the trust shift it creates,"},{"time":991880,"text":"and for my part, I want to help people\nunderstand this new era of trust"},{"time":997000,"text":"so that we can get it right"},{"time":998680,"text":"and we can embrace\nthe opportunities to redesign systems"},{"time":1002600,"text":"that are more transparent,\ninclusive and accountable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1006720,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1008000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1010600,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1011840,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}